President Muhammadu Buhari visited Zaria, Kaduna State on Thursday, during which he inaugurated some projects, and also received a horse as gift. The President had visited the Emir of Zazzau, Dr. Shehu Idris, who presented a horse to him as gift. The President, during the visit, was also at the Ahmadu Bello University, Zaria, where he inaugurated the postgraduate Centre of Excellence built by the Central Bank of Nigeria. Buhari then inaugurated the Zaria Water supply expansion, which will reportedly serve over two million people in the ancient city of Zaria and its surroundings. See the President’s Zaria visit in Twitter/Instagram photographs: The Zaria Water supply expansion project